.:: Einstein-puzzle ::.

The people use 5 different means of transport: quad-bike, bike, car, ship, trike
The people have 5 different hobbies: singing, fishing, baking, dancing, board-games
City: london, new-york, marseilles, berlin, hamburg
5 different games are played: quad-bikemaster, go, domino, whist, bridge
5 different pets are kept: cat, bird, dog, fish, horse
1. the person who's hobby is singing is the person driving the car
2. the person who's hobby is swedish is the owner of the dog
3. the person who's hobby is fishing is the person traveling to berlin
4. the person driving the bike is on the left of the person driving the ship
5. the person driving the bike is the person traveling to new-york
6. the person playing domino is the owner of the bird
7. the person driving the trike is the person playing go
8. the person traveling to marseilles is in the middle
9. the person who's hobby is dancing is on the far left
10. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the owner of the cat
11. the owner of the horses is on the left or right of the person playing go
12. the person playing quad-bikemaster is the person traveling to london
13. the person who's hobby is baking is the person playing whist
14. the person who's hobby is dancing is on the left or right of the person driving the quad-bike
15. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person traveling to hamburg

.:: Answer ::.
|		|	1	|	2	|	3	|	4	|	5	|
| Transport		|    trike	|     quad-bike	|      car	|     bike	|     ship	|
| Hobby	|   dancing	|    fishing	|    singing	|    baking	|    swedish	|
| Pet		|     cat	|    horse	|     bird	|     fish	|      dog	|
| City	|    hamburg	|     berlin	|     marseilles	|    new-york	|      london	|
| Game		|   go	|    bridge	|  domino	|    whist	|   quad-bikemaster	|
